When rendering DiffClosureResult or DiffAllResult, each node side is annotated with its role in the closure: [SEED] when the node ID matches one of the closure's event Seed fields (the node that originated the closure), or [citer] when the node was pulled in by propagation. The label appears inline immediately after the entity ID, matching the placement convention of [deleted] / [unlinked] / [DRIFTED] tags elsewhere. The rule is uniform across Plain, Color, and JSON presenters. JSON encodes the role as a boolean IsSeed field on each diff side. See <ref spec="cli.diff_command">diff command</ref>.